column49: The "Book Finder" doesn't include a way to search by reading level or binding (e.g. hardcover, softcover). My child is in 1st grade, but reads several years above grade level. The book finder gave us suggestions that were not appropriate for her.    As a parent, I would also love an option that allows me to select for, or against, franchised characters. In general, books with those characters are not very strong in terms of story (since they're trading off the "familiarity factor"), and we don't like to promote TV shows through our reading. It would be nice if we could select for that.

column49: I have been a loyal customer for 30 years.  I am thoroughly disappointed with the quality of books you have available under $2.  For several years now I have asked people in our community to sponsor our students at $2 per month per child to get them the much needed books they need in their homes.  I used to be very proud of the books I could send home with my students.  Now the books that are available in that price range are tiny leftover books that were previously sold as a set- I know because I have some of those sets in my classroom and they were cheaper as the entire set, not just a small portion of the book sets as are being offered now.  I am also frustrated that you no longer offer Book of the Week or books for a dollar.  This has me seriously considering stopping my patronage of your company and no longer asking the community to sponsor students for such a poor offering as you currently have. At the top of this form you say you value my feedback, but do you really??

column49: Your cart does not allow autofill programs to work.  This makes the process tedious.    It was unclear how to register because there were two options.  Originally I had a teacher account, which I had to delete to create the correct parent account with my email (the email could only be used once, which forced me to figure out how to delete the account).      The screens to locate your teacher were small and hard to use.  An endless long list in a scroll menu just isn't good UI design.  Also, my students school was hard to find because it the name wasn't complete.   You really really need a direct link or QR code to a specific teacher.  It's clear to me this was designed by a tech person, and not a user who need to navigate some 5000 schools to find a specific school.  Also, the is necessary to order, which seems ridiculous.
